1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 11-28.3-06 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to rural ambulance board compensation.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 11-28.3-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 11-28.3-06. Organization - Board of directors.
7 1. At the time and place fixed by the county auditor for the public meeting as provided in
8 section 11-28.3-05, the qualified electors present who reside within the boundaries of
9 the district shall proceed to organize the district. Permanent organization must be
10 effected by the election of a board of directors consisting of not less than five nor more
11 than ten residents of the district. The board of directors shall meet as soon after the
12 organizational meeting as possible to elect a president, a vice president, and a
13 secretary-treasurer.
14 2. All directors and officers must be elected for two years and hold office until their
15 successors have been elected and qualified, except that at the first election the vice
16 president must be elected as provided in this section for a one-year term, and
17 one-half, or as close to one-half as possible depending upon the total number of
18 directors, of the directors elected at the first election after July 1, 1977, must be
19 selected by lot in the presence of a majority of such directors to serve one-year terms.
20 3. A district may specify in its bylaws a specified number of directors within the limitations
21 in this section, provided each township or group of townships receives equal
22 representation on the board with respect to the regions. The bylaws also may allow for
23 a combination of regional directors and at-large directors.
